As the criticism of Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane’s proposal to change the mandate of the South African Reserve Bank (Sarb) mounted, ratings agency S&P’s Global Ratings yesterday weighed in on the matter, warning against the meddling with the central bank’s independence. ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
